. do "$code/table_bh_ri.do"

. *============================================================================
> ===
. * table_bh_ri.do — Borusyak-Hull (2021) Randomization Inference
. *
. * Uses ri_pvalue.ado and ri_ci.ado (copied from BH replication package)
. * to test whether the procurement markup premium survives randomization
. * inference under counterfactual treatment assignments.
. *============================================================================
> ===
. 
. dis _newline "--- table_bh_ri.do ---"

--- table_bh_ri.do ---

. 
. * Add ado path
. adopath + "$root/ado"
  [1]  (BASE)      "/Applications/StataNow/ado/base/"
  [2]  (SITE)      "/Applications/StataNow/ado/site/"
  [3]              "."
  [4]  (PERSONAL)  "/Users/marek/Documents/Stata/ado/personal/"
  [5]  (PLUS)      "/Users/marek/Library/Application Support/Stata/ado/plus/"
  [6]  (OLDPLACE)  "~/ado/"
  [7]              "./ado"

. 
. * Load from markups_panel.dta (created by calculate_markups.do).
. * It has l_mu_A plus pp_dummy, k, cogs, nace2, year, id — everything this
. * script needs. analysis_panel.dta lacks l_mu_A because markup calculation
. * runs after prepare_data.do.
. use "$data/markups_panel.dta", clear

. xtset id year, yearly

Panel variable: id (unbalanced)
 Time variable: year, 2006 to 2021, but with gaps
         Delta: 1 year

. 
. * Year × NACE absorbing interaction (for reghdfe / ri_pvalue absorb)
. cap drop yr_nace

. egen yr_nace = group(year nace2)

. 
. drop if missing(l_mu_A, pp_dummy, k, cogs)
(0 observations deleted)

. 
. * ── Generate counterfactual treatment assignments ──
. * Strategy: permute pp_dummy within (year, nace2) strata
. * K=500 permutations (Stata is slower than Python's 1000)
. 
. set seed 42

. local K = 500

. 
. * Create strata
. egen strata = group(year nace2)

. 
. * Sort-based permutation: sorting by random number within strata
. * effectively shuffles pp_dummy within each stratum
. forvalues s = 1/`K' {
  2.     tempvar rand
  3.     gen `rand' = runiform()
  4.     bys strata (`rand'): gen pp_sim_`s' = pp_dummy[_n]
  5.     drop `rand'
  6.     if mod(`s', 100) == 0 dis "  Permutation `s'/`K' done"
  7. }
  Permutation 100/500 done
  Permutation 200/500 done
  Permutation 300/500 done
  Permutation 400/500 done
  Permutation 500/500 done

. 
. dis "  Generated `K' permuted treatment assignments"
  Generated 500 permuted treatment assignments

. 
. * ── Run BH randomization inference ──
. 
. * RI p-value (null: premium = 0)
. ri_pvalue l_mu_A pp_dummy, zsim(pp_sim_*) beta(0) controls(k cogs) absorb(yr_
> nace)

. local ri_p = r(pvalue)

. local ri_stat = r(stat)

. local ri_nsims = r(nsims)

. dis _newline "  RI p-value: " `ri_p' " (stat=" `ri_stat' ", nsims=" `ri_nsims
> ' ")"

  RI p-value: 0 (stat=252.13555, nsims=500)

. 
. * RI confidence interval (search range: -0.1 to 0.4)
. ri_ci l_mu_A pp_dummy, zsim(pp_sim_*) range(-0.1 0.4) controls(k cogs) absorb
> (yr_nace)
Warning: CI is empty

. local ci_lo = r(ci_left)

. local ci_hi = r(ci_right)

. dis "  RI 95% CI: [" `ci_lo' ", " `ci_hi' "]"
  RI 95% CI: [., .]

. 
. * Standard OLS for comparison
. reghdfe l_mu_A pp_dummy k cogs, absorb(yr_nace) cluster(id)
(MWFE estimator converged in 1 iterations)

HDFE Linear regression                            Number of obs   =      9,164
Absorbing 1 HDFE group                            F(   3,   1497) =    1704.27
Statistics robust to heteroskedasticity           Prob > F        =     0.0000
                                                  R-squared       =     0.9572
                                                  Adj R-squared   =     0.9570
                                                  Within R-sq.    =     0.6807
Number of clusters (id)      =      1,498         Root MSE        =     0.0576

                                 (Std. err. adjusted for 1,498 clusters in id)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
             |               Robust
      l_mu_A | Coefficient  std. err.      t    P>|t|     [95% conf. interval]
-------------+----------------------------------------------------------------
    pp_dummy |   .1407067   .0024521    57.38   0.000     .1358968    .1455165
           k |    .043385   .0013332    32.54   0.000     .0407698    .0460002
        cogs |  -.0605113   .0033083   -18.29   0.000    -.0670007   -.0540219
       _cons |   1.128813   .0486618    23.20   0.000      1.03336    1.224265
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Absorbed degrees of freedom:
-----------------------------------------------------+
 Absorbed FE | Categories  - Redundant  = Num. Coefs |
-------------+---------------------------------------|
     yr_nace |        48           0          48     |
-----------------------------------------------------+

. local ols_b = _b[pp_dummy]

. local ols_se = _se[pp_dummy]

. local ols_lo = `ols_b' - 1.96 * `ols_se'

. local ols_hi = `ols_b' + 1.96 * `ols_se'

. 
. dis _newline "  === Comparison ==="

  === Comparison ===

. dis "  OLS:     " %6.4f `ols_b' " [" %6.4f `ols_lo' ", " %6.4f `ols_hi' "]"
  OLS:     0.1407 [0.1359, 0.1455]

. dis "  BH RI:   " %6.4f `ols_b' " [" %6.4f `ci_lo' ", " %6.4f `ci_hi' "] p=" 
> %6.4f `ri_p'
  BH RI:   0.1407 [     .,      .] p=0.0000

. 
. * Save results to CSV
. tempname fh

. file open `fh' using "$output/bh_ri_stata.csv", write replace
(file ../../output/stata/bh_ri_stata.csv not found)

. file write `fh' "method,estimate,ci_lo,ci_hi,pvalue" _n

. file write `fh' "OLS clustered," %6.4f (`ols_b') "," %6.4f (`ols_lo') "," %6.
> 4f (`ols_hi') ",." _n

. file write `fh' "BH RI (within yr x nace)," %6.4f (`ols_b') "," %6.4f (`ci_lo
> ') "," %6.4f (`ci_hi') "," %6.4f (`ri_p') _n

. file close `fh'

. 
. dis _newline "--- table_bh_ri.do DONE ---"

--- table_bh_ri.do DONE ---

. 
end of do-file

